nding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the premium index method. The rate is determined by the 8-hour time-weighted average premium between the perpetual and spot price. Funding payments occur automatically between long and short position holders based on the calculated rate. Phemex applies a ±0.375% funding rate cap to limit extreme payments during volatile periods."}]]}],"$L3",["$L4","$L5","$L6"],"$L7"]}],"$L8"]}]]}],["$L9","$La"],"$Lb"]}],"loading":null,"isPartial":false}
3:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BLUR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR's connection to NFT marketplace dynamics creates unique funding rate patterns driven by speculation around NFT trading volumes and marketplace adoption. The token's relatively small market cap amplifies funding rate volatility, offering higher potential returns for skilled arbitrageurs. However, this volatility also increases position management complexity compared to major cryptocurrency pairs."}]]}]
4:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR/USDT funding rates on Phemex typically range from -0.5% to +2% daily, with spikes during NFT market rallies or Blur protocol updates. Rates often turn negative during broader crypto downturns when long liquidations dominate. Weekend periods frequently show reduced volatility as NFT trading activity decreases. The token's correlation with Ethereum gas prices and NFT collection floor prices creates predictable rate movements around major NFT events."}]]}]
5:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Phemex's low 0.01% maker fees enable profitable arbitrage even on smaller funding rate differentials compared to higher-fee exchanges. Cross-exchange arbitrage between Phemex and Binance or OKX can be particularly effective during BLUR rate spikes. The 8-hour funding interval provides sufficient time for position adjustments and hedging strategies. Delta-neutral strategies work well given BLUR's moderate liquidity and Phemex's efficient order matching engine."}]]}]
6:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR's smaller market cap creates higher liquidation risks during unexpected price movements, especially around NFT marketplace announcements. Phemex's relatively smaller user base can lead to liquidity gaps during volatile periods, affecting position entry and exit. The token's correlation with NFT sector sentiment means positions can be impacted by broader digital collectibles market trends beyond pure funding rate dynamics. Weekend and late-night Asian hours often show reduced liquidity, increasing slippage risks for larger positions."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical BLUR funding rates on Phemex?","answer":"BLUR/USDT funding rates on Phemex typically range from -0.2% to +0.8% per 8-hour period, with occasional spikes above 1% during NFT market rallies. Negative rates are common during crypto bear markets when short interest dominates."},{"question":"How does Phemex's maker fee structure affect BLUR arbitrage?","answer":"Phemex's 0.01% maker fees significantly reduce arbitrage costs compared to exchanges charging 0.02-0.04%. This lower fee structure makes BLUR funding rate arbitrage profitable even on smaller rate differentials of 0.1-0.2% per funding period."},{"question":"What NFT market events impact BLUR funding rates most?","answer":"Major NFT collection launches, Blur protocol updates, and changes to marketplace fee structures typically drive the highest funding rate volatility. OpenSea policy changes and Ethereum gas price spikes also create significant rate movements."},{"question":"Is BLUR liquidity sufficient for funding rate strategies on Phemex?","answer":"BLUR/USDT maintains adequate liquidity for positions up to $50,000 during regular trading hours. However, liquidity can thin during Asian overnight hours and weekends, requiring careful position sizing and timing for larger arbitrage strategies."}]}]
